President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster for the Oglala Sioux Tribe and authorized Federal aid to support their efforts in areas affected by a severe winter storm, snowstorm, and flooding from March 13 to March 26, 2019. The Federal funding will be available to the Tribe and certain nonprofit organizations for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, snow assistance for a continuous 48-hour period, and hazard mitigation measures. James R. Stephenson has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further damage assessments may lead to additional designations in the future. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.